  <h2>about the website:</h2>

  <p>This website stores and presents various projects. It originally got up and running thanks to Jonathan McGlone's wonderfully helpful <a href="http://jmcglone.com/guides/github-pages/">guide</a>.</p>

  <p>The site is now built with <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a>, hosted on a personal server (Debian Testing on a ThinkPad X230), and encrypted by <a href="https://letsencrypt.org/">Let's Encrypt</a>/<a href="https://certbot.eff.org/">Certbot</a>.</p>

  <h3>installation</h3>

  <p>The <a href="https://github.com/lbeckman314/website">website's source code</a> is yours. Feel free to copy and paste, fork, clone, or anything you like! To spin up your own site, follow the Astro quick-start guide (adapted below) —</p>

  <pre><code class="language-shell"># Install Node.js
# for OS-specific instructions, check out https://nodejs.org/

# Clone the site
git clone https://github.com/lbeckman314/website

# Change into your new directory
cd website

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Build the site on the preview server
npm run dev

# Now browse to http://localhost:4321

# Then you can change the astro/html/css files to suit your tastes!

# Hosting is a whole 'nother beast, but services like github pages, netlify, and vercel make free hosting relatively easier.
# self-hosting with apache and/or nginx is another cool possibility!</code></pre>
